LOCUS       NG_011626               9488 bp    DNA     linear   PRI 10-APR-2026
DEFINITION  Homo sapiens atypical chemokine receptor 1 (Duffy blood group)
            (ACKR1), RefSeqGene (LRG_801) on chromosome 1.
ACCESSION   NG_011626
VERSION     NG_011626.3
KEYWORDS    RefSeq; RefSeqGene.
SOURCE      Homo sapiens (human)
  ORGANISM  Homo sapiens
            Eukaryota; Metazoa; Chordata; Craniata; Vertebrata; Euteleostomi;
            Mammalia; Eutheria; Euarchontoglires; Primates; Haplorrhini;
            Catarrhini; Hominidae; Homo.
COMMENT     REVIEWED REFSEQ: This record has been curated by NCBI staff in
            collaboration with Jill R. Storry. The reference sequence was
            derived from AL035403.10 and KF455042.1.
            This sequence is a reference standard in the RefSeqGene project.
            
            On Mar 29, 2017 this sequence version replaced NG_011626.2.
            
            Summary: The protein encoded by this gene is a glycosylated
            membrane protein and a non-specific receptor for several
            chemokines. The encoded protein is the receptor for the human
            malarial parasites Plasmodium vivax and Plasmodium knowlesi.
            Polymorphisms in this gene are the basis of the Duffy blood group
            system. Two transcript variants encoding different isoforms have
            been found for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008].
